### Journey Map / Service Blueprint

Use this section when the artifact includes a journey map, service blueprint, or user flow. Prefer Mermaid so the diagram stays reviewable in Markdown; link Figma or Miro only when the source diagram must remain in a design board.
Mermaid safety: avoid semicolons and raw pipes in labels, keep brackets/quotes balanced, and use ` - ` or `,` instead of `;`.

```mermaid
journey
  title User Journey - <journey name>
  section Discover
    Identify need: 3: User
    Review requirements: 4: User
  section Complete Task
    Start request: 3: User
    Resolve blockers: 2: User
    Submit request: 5: User
  section Follow Up
    Track status: 4: User
    Receive outcome: 5: User
```

### User Flow / System Touchpoints

Use Mermaid-safe labels for every node and edge. Quote labels that contain punctuation, slashes, or parentheses.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A["Trigger / user need"] --> B["Entry point / screen"]
  B --> C["Primary action"]
  C --> D{"Decision or validation"}
  D -->|Success| E["Outcome"]
  D -->|Error| F["Error recovery"]
  D -->|Abandon| G["Abandon / save state"]
```

